A 15-YEAR-OLD girl is in hospital with neck and spinal injuries after falling 60 feet from a Lothian cliff edge.Fire crews, coastguard teams and an RAF helicopter were scrambled to an area of beach below Dunbar Castle, East Lothian, following reports of the youngster's fall earlier this afternoon.The teenager was airlifted to Edinburgh Royal Infirmary shortly before 4pm.It is not known how serious her injuries are.Coast guard rescuers said the circumstances surrounding the fall were unclear. They said she might have got too close to the edge.